00:21:22,070 --> 00:21:24,600
I think I can speak like this when I need
someone new.

573
00:21:25,160 --> 00:21:26,160
Yes, you can.

574
00:21:26,505 --> 00:21:29,040
You just need to remember small sentence
patterns.

575
00:21:29,660 --> 00:21:31,240
For example, I like.

576
00:21:31,920 --> 00:21:32,920
I go.

577
00:21:33,220 --> 00:21:34,220
I do.

578
00:21:34,440 --> 00:21:35,440
I have.

579
00:21:35,660 --> 00:21:36,660
Let's practice with those.

580
00:21:36,661 --> 00:21:38,040
Okay, sir.

581
00:21:38,600 --> 00:21:39,600
Say after me.

582
00:21:40,340 --> 00:21:41,340
I like tea.

583
00:21:41,960 --> 00:21:42,960
I like tea.

584
00:21:43,820 --> 00:21:45,000
I go to school.

585
00:21:45,830 --> 00:21:46,940
I go to school.

586
00:21:47,860 --> 00:21:49,060
I do my homework.

587
00:21:49,920 --> 00:21:51,140
I do my homework.

588
00:21:52,060 --> 00:21:53,580
I have many friends.

589
00:21:54,540 --> 00:21:56,220
I have many friends.

590
00:21:56,520 --> 00:21:57,520
Good.

591
00:21:57,965 --> 00:22:00,840
You can use these short patterns to make
many sentences.

592
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:03,780
For example, I like apples.

593
00:22:04,700 --> 00:22:05,740
I go to the park.

594
00:22:06,490 --> 00:22:07,700
I do my work.

595
00:22:08,445 --> 00:22:09,540
I have a brother.

596
00:22:10,160 --> 00:22:11,160
Yes, sir.

597
00:22:11,590 --> 00:22:12,760
I can make many now.

598
00:22:13,120 --> 00:22:14,120
I like chocolate.

599
00:22:15,040 --> 00:22:16,160
I go to the market.

600
00:22:16,990 --> 00:22:18,200
I do my homework.

601
00:22:19,240 --> 00:22:20,240
I have a sister.

602
00:22:20,740 --> 00:22:21,740
Excellent.

603
00:22:22,290 --> 00:22:23,450
You are using them correctly.

604
00:22:24,300 --> 00:22:25,580
That's how you build confidence.

605
00:22:26,660 --> 00:22:29,960
Now, let's make some questions using do
and does.

606
00:22:30,670 --> 00:22:38,420
Remember, we use do for I, you,
we, they and does for he, she,

607
00:22:39,040 --> 00:22:39,160
it.

608
00:22:39,950 --> 00:22:44,360
For example, do you like coffee or does he
play football?

609
00:22:45,120 --> 00:22:46,120
Okay, sir.

610
00:22:46,560 --> 00:22:47,560
Let me try.

611
00:22:48,600 --> 00:22:49,600
Do you like music?

612
00:22:50,580 --> 00:22:51,580
Yes, I do.

613
00:22:52,415 --> 00:22:53,860
Does she go to school?

614
00:22:53,861 --> 00:22:55,360
Yes, she does.

615
00:22:56,485 --> 00:22:57,680
Do they play football?

616
00:22:58,690 --> 00:22:59,690
No, they don't.

617
00:23:00,330 --> 00:23:01,330
Do you read books?

618
00:23:02,300 --> 00:23:03,300
Yes, I do.

619
00:23:03,960 --> 00:23:04,960
Very good.

620
00:23:05,445 --> 00:23:06,980
Now you are making questions.

621
00:23:07,540 --> 00:23:09,100
That's how we have real conversations.

622
00:23:10,045 --> 00:23:12,420
You can use these every day with friends.

623
00:23:13,140 --> 00:23:16,360
Sir, sometimes I feel scared to ask
questions.

624
00:23:17,120 --> 00:23:18,120
That's normal.

625
00:23:18,550 --> 00:23:21,180
But the more you ask, the easier it
becomes.

626
00:23:21,905 --> 00:23:24,080
People will answer and you will learn from
them.

627
00:23:24,720 --> 00:23:27,380
If you make a mistake, just smile and
continue.

628
00:23:27,940 --> 00:23:28,940
Yes, sir.

629
00:23:29,090 --> 00:23:30,240
I will try to talk more.

630
00:23:30,780 --> 00:23:31,780
Great.

631
00:23:31,950 --> 00:23:34,100
Let's practice talking about your family
now.

632
00:23:34,790 --> 00:23:37,080
Tell me about your family in simple
sentences.

633
00:23:38,050 --> 00:23:39,820
I have four people in my family.

634
00:23:40,680 --> 00:23:42,160
My father works in an office.

635
00:23:42,940 --> 00:23:44,260
My mother cooks food.

636
00:23:44,865 --> 00:23:46,260
My brother studies in school.

637
00:23:47,160 --> 00:23:48,160
I study English.

638
00:23:48,980 --> 00:23:49,980
Excellent.

639
00:23:50,430 --> 00:23:51,980
Now, let's add some more details.

640
00:23:53,160 --> 00:23:54,860
What time does your father go to work?

641
00:23:55,940 --> 00:23:58,160
He goes to work at nine o'clock.

642
00:23:58,860 --> 00:24:00,000
What time does he come home?

643
00:24:00,770 --> 00:24:02,640
He comes home at six o'clock.

644
00:24:02,840 --> 00:24:03,840
Good.

645
00:24:04,290 --> 00:24:05,980
What does your mother do in the afternoon?

646
00:24:06,830 --> 00:24:09,180
She cooks lunch and cleans the house.

647
00:24:09,880 --> 00:24:10,880
Very good.

648
00:24:11,145 --> 00:24:14,920
You are using does and s endings
correctly.

649
00:24:15,920 --> 00:24:17,000
That's a big improvement.

650
00:24:17,920 --> 00:24:18,920
Thank you, sir.

651
00:24:19,620 --> 00:24:20,720
I remember your examples.

652
00:24:22,180 --> 00:24:24,120
That's the key to learning.

653
00:24:25,300 --> 00:24:26,660
Listen and repeat.

654
00:24:27,485 --> 00:24:28,820
Repeat every day.

655
00:24:29,495 --> 00:24:33,240
When you repeat, your tongue becomes
comfortable with English sounds.

656
00:24:33,980 --> 00:24:35,300
Let's repeat a few more.

657
00:24:36,340 --> 00:24:37,900
He works in an office.

658
00:24:41,560 --> 00:24:42,860
She cooks dinner.

659
00:24:43,620 --> 00:24:44,840
She cooks dinner.

660
00:24:45,820 --> 00:24:47,020
He reads books.

661
00:24:48,070 --> 00:24:51,920
She watches TV.

662
00:24:52,880 --> 00:24:54,400
She watches TV.

663
00:24:55,100 --> 00:24:56,100
Very good.

664
00:24:56,620 --> 00:24:59,180
These are simple but useful sentences.

665
00:24:59,181 --> 00:25:02,900
You can talk about anyone using these.

666
00:25:03,660 --> 00:25:04,660
Yes, sir.

667
00:25:05,260 --> 00:25:08,840
I can talk about my family, my friends,
or my teacher.

668
00:25:09,680 --> 00:25:10,680
Exactly.

669
00:25:11,090 --> 00:25:13,920
Now, let's talk about likes and dislikes.

670
00:25:14,760 --> 00:25:16,760
This is also in simple, present tense.

671
00:25:17,520 --> 00:25:19,380
You can say, I like apples.

672
00:25:20,260 --> 00:25:21,260
I don't like bananas.

673
00:25:22,420 --> 00:25:23,420
She likes tea.

674
00:25:24,100 --> 00:25:25,180
He doesn't like milk.

675
00:25:26,180 --> 00:25:27,180
Try some.

676
00:25:27,320 --> 00:25:28,320
I like chocolate.

677
00:25:29,120 --> 00:25:30,620
I don't like coffee.

678
00:25:31,400 --> 00:25:32,400
She likes music.

679
00:25:33,260 --> 00:25:34,260
He doesn't like noise.

680
00:25:35,020 --> 00:25:36,020
Very nice.

681
00:25:36,600 --> 00:25:37,880
You said everything correctly.

682
00:25:38,680 --> 00:25:42,600
Remember, when we use doesn't,
we don't add s to the verb.

683
00:25:43,120 --> 00:25:45,180
For example, he doesn't like.

684
00:25:45,840 --> 00:25:47,600
Not he doesn't likes.

685
00:25:48,480 --> 00:25:49,080
Yes, sir.

686
00:25:49,480 --> 00:25:50,480
I understand.

687
00:25:51,100 --> 00:25:52,100
Good.

688
00:25:52,370 --> 00:25:54,620
Let's add a few small dialogues now.

689
00:25:55,140 --> 00:25:56,840
I'll say something and you answer.

690
00:25:57,760 --> 00:25:58,760
Do you like English?

691
00:25:59,460 --> 00:26:00,480
Yes, I do.

692
00:26:01,350 --> 00:26:02,900
What do you do every morning?

693
00:26:03,560 --> 00:26:04,560
I wake up early.

694
00:26:05,440 --> 00:26:06,440
I brush my teeth.

695
00:26:07,400 --> 00:26:08,400
I eat breakfast.

696
00:26:09,020 --> 00:26:10,380
Where do you go after breakfast?

697
00:26:11,320 --> 00:26:12,320
I go to school.

698
00:26:13,140 --> 00:26:14,560
What do you do in the evening?

699
00:26:15,480 --> 00:26:19,060
I study English and listen to songs.

700
00:26:19,760 --> 00:26:20,760
Excellent.

701
00:26:21,150 --> 00:26:22,800
You are talking naturally now.

702
00:26:23,430 --> 00:26:25,360
This is how conversations happen.

703
00:26:25,880 --> 00:26:28,140
Simple, short, clear.

704
00:26:29,100 --> 00:26:31,800
I feel happy when I can answer without
stopping.

705
00:26:32,480 --> 00:26:33,480
That's great.

706
00:26:33,880 --> 00:26:34,880
You should feel proud.

707
00:26:35,540 --> 00:26:37,420
Every small step makes you better.

708
00:26:38,270 --> 00:26:40,220
Keep using the simple present tense.

709
00:26:40,800 --> 00:26:45,740
It helps you talk about your life,
your habits, your family, and your likes.

710
00:26:46,580 --> 00:26:47,580
Yes, sir.

711
00:26:47,880 --> 00:26:49,260
I can feel I am learning.

712
00:26:50,100 --> 00:26:51,100
You are.

713
00:26:51,280 --> 00:26:56,240
Just remember to speak slowly,
think in English, and use small sentences.

714
00:26:57,155 --> 00:27:01,820
Every day you can start your morning with
10 sentences like, I wake up.

715
00:27:02,380 --> 00:27:03,380
I eat breakfast.

716
00:27:03,720 --> 00:27:04,720
I go to school.

717
00:27:05,100 --> 00:27:06,100
I study.

718
00:27:06,240 --> 00:27:07,240
I come home.

719
00:27:07,500 --> 00:27:08,500
I watch TV.

720
00:27:09,190 --> 00:27:11,180
That will make your English natural.

721
00:27:11,940 --> 00:27:12,940
I will do that.

722
00:27:13,370 --> 00:27:16,000
I will speak every day and not be shy.

723
00:27:17,060 --> 00:27:18,200
That's very good.

724
00:27:18,870 --> 00:27:21,560
Keep going and you will become more
confident.

725
00:27:22,540 --> 00:27:25,120
Sir, I want to tell you something.

726
00:27:25,920 --> 00:27:31,580
Yesterday, when I spoke English with my
classmates, they laughed at me again.

727
00:27:32,520 --> 00:27:33,720
I felt very bad.

728
00:27:34,650 --> 00:27:36,020
I wanted to stop speaking.

729
00:27:37,160 --> 00:27:39,440
I think my English is not good.

730
00:27:40,190 --> 00:27:42,140
Oh, I understand how you feel.

731
00:27:42,880 --> 00:27:44,840
It hurts when people laugh, doesn't it?

732
00:27:45,550 --> 00:27:48,220
But listen, that doesn't mean your English
is bad.

733
00:27:48,960 --> 00:27:51,520
It means you are trying and they are not.

734
00:27:52,200 --> 00:27:55,440
You are learning and that is something to
be proud of.

735
00:27:55,840 --> 00:27:59,440
But sir, when I talk, I forget words.

736
00:28:00,260 --> 00:28:01,640
My mind goes blank.

737
00:28:02,520 --> 00:28:04,980
I start one sentence and then stop.

738
00:28:05,790 --> 00:28:07,080
Everyone looks at me.

739
00:28:07,680 --> 00:28:09,080
I feel so small.

740
00:28:09,980 --> 00:28:10,980
That's okay.

741
00:28:11,660 --> 00:28:13,060
Every learner feels that way.

742
00:28:14,020 --> 00:28:16,020
Even native speakers forget words
sometimes.

743
00:28:16,960 --> 00:28:18,380
You are learning a new language.

744
00:28:19,140 --> 00:28:20,340
You must make mistakes.

745
00:28:20,341 --> 00:28:22,280
Mistakes are not bad.

746
00:28:22,940 --> 00:28:24,020
They are part of learning.

747
00:28:24,620 --> 00:28:26,520
Without mistakes, we can't grow.

748
00:28:27,460 --> 00:28:31,220
Sometimes I think maybe English is not for
me.

749
00:28:31,900 --> 00:28:34,000
Maybe I can never speak well.

750
00:28:34,860 --> 00:28:36,120
No, don't say that.

751
00:28:36,500 --> 00:28:37,500
You already speak.

752
00:28:38,040 --> 00:28:40,660
You were talking to me now and I
understand you.

753
00:28:41,120 --> 00:28:42,440
That means you can speak.

754
00:28:43,080 --> 00:28:45,260
You just need more practice and more
confidence.

755
00:28:46,240 --> 00:28:48,880
When you speak, don't think about what
people say.

756
00:28:49,500 --> 00:28:51,300
Just think about what you want to say.

757
00:28:52,100 --> 00:28:55,960
But sir, when people laugh, it makes me
nervous.

758
00:28:56,780 --> 00:28:57,780
My hands shake.

759
00:28:58,300 --> 00:28:59,420
I forget everything.

760
00:29:00,710 --> 00:29:01,780
That's normal too.

761
00:29:02,600 --> 00:29:03,840
Many people feel nervous.

762
00:29:04,620 --> 00:29:06,420
You can train your mind to stay calm.

763
00:29:07,220 --> 00:29:10,300
Take a deep breath, smile and speak
slowly.

764
00:29:10,980 --> 00:29:12,200
You don't have to speak fast.

765
00:29:13,120 --> 00:29:14,920
Clear and slow English is better.

766
00:29:15,810 --> 00:29:18,060
I try to speak fast like others.

767
00:29:18,800 --> 00:29:20,320
Maybe that's my mistake.

768
00:29:21,150 --> 00:29:23,580
Yes, you don't need to copy others.

769
00:29:24,260 --> 00:29:25,720
Speak at your own speed.

770
00:29:26,390 --> 00:29:27,580
Let's practice something now.

771
00:29:28,300 --> 00:29:31,260
When you talk about your day, use short
sentences.

772
00:29:32,300 --> 00:29:34,160
You can say, I wake up.

773
00:29:34,780 --> 00:29:35,780
I brush my teeth.

774
00:29:36,220 --> 00:29:37,220
I eat breakfast.

775
00:29:37,320 --> 00:29:38,320
I go to school.

776
00:29:38,800 --> 00:29:39,800
Say it with me.

777
00:29:40,160 --> 00:29:41,160
I wake up.

778
00:29:41,470 --> 00:29:42,470
I brush my teeth.

779
00:29:43,360 --> 00:29:44,360
I eat breakfast.

780
00:29:44,800 --> 00:29:45,800
I go to school.

781
00:29:46,180 --> 00:29:47,180
Good.

782
00:29:47,430 --> 00:29:48,640
Simple and clear.

783
00:29:49,200 --> 00:29:50,200
That's beautiful English.

784
00:29:50,935 --> 00:29:55,020
You see, you are already speaking
correctly in the simple present tense.

785
00:29:55,680 --> 00:29:56,680
Yes, sir.

786
00:29:57,330 --> 00:29:59,340
I can say these sentences easily.

787
00:30:00,500 --> 00:30:03,080
That's because these are daily routine
actions.

788
00:30:03,910 --> 00:30:06,400
The more you say them, the easier it
becomes.

789
00:30:07,180 --> 00:30:08,580
Now let's add a few more.

790
00:30:09,155 --> 00:30:10,155
I come home.

791
00:30:10,380 --> 00:30:11,380
I eat lunch.

792
00:30:11,900 --> 00:30:12,900
I do my homework.

793
00:30:13,360 --> 00:30:14,360
I take a rest.

794
00:30:14,740 --> 00:30:15,740
I watch TV.

795
00:30:16,420 --> 00:30:17,420
I sleep.

796
00:30:17,780 --> 00:30:18,780
I come home.

797
00:30:19,280 --> 00:30:20,280
I eat lunch.

798
00:30:20,880 --> 00:30:21,940
I do my homework.

799
00:30:22,580 --> 00:30:23,580
I take a rest.

800
00:30:24,140 --> 00:30:25,140
I watch TV.

801
00:30:25,800 --> 00:30:26,800
I sleep.

802
00:30:26,840 --> 00:30:27,840
Very good.

803
00:30:28,200 --> 00:30:30,680
You see, you can describe your full day.

804
00:30:31,260 --> 00:30:35,660
Now, if someone asks, what do you do every
day, you can answer easily.

805
00:30:36,410 --> 00:30:37,410
Yes, sir.

806
00:30:37,570 --> 00:30:39,980
I can say, I wake up early.

807
00:30:40,700 --> 00:30:41,700
I brush my teeth.

808
00:30:42,260 --> 00:30:43,260
I go to school.

809
00:30:43,620 --> 00:30:44,620
I study.

810
00:30:44,800 --> 00:30:45,800
I come home.

811
00:30:45,980 --> 00:30:46,980
I eat lunch.

812
00:30:47,300 --> 00:30:48,300
I watch TV.

813
00:30:48,800 --> 00:30:49,120
I sleep.

814
00:30:49,760 --> 00:30:50,760
Perfect.

815
00:30:51,220 --> 00:30:53,780
You just spoke eight correct sentences in
English.

816
00:30:54,500 --> 00:30:55,500
Thank you, sir.

817
00:30:56,020 --> 00:30:58,840
When I speak slowly like this,
I feel better.

818
00:30:59,840 --> 00:31:00,840
That's the right way.

819
00:31:01,660 --> 00:31:05,380
Always speak slowly, clearly, and
confidently.

820
00:31:06,400 --> 00:31:08,580
Remember, English is not a race.

821
00:31:09,260 --> 00:31:10,260
It's a skill.

822
00:31:10,620 --> 00:31:12,840
You build it step by step.

823
00:31:13,140 --> 00:31:18,940
Sir, sometimes I also forget when to use S
with verbs.

824
00:31:19,840 --> 00:31:22,880
Like he play or he plays.

825
00:31:23,840 --> 00:31:24,840
I get confused.

826
00:31:25,950 --> 00:31:27,400
That's a very common mistake.

827
00:31:28,180 --> 00:31:29,180
Let's practice it.

828
00:31:29,760 --> 00:31:37,821
In simple present tense, when we talk
about he, she, or it, we add S to the verb.

829
00:31:38,030 --> 00:31:40,380
For example, he plays football.

830
00:31:41,460 --> 00:31:42,580
She cooks food.

831
00:31:43,340 --> 00:31:44,680
It rains in summer.

832
00:31:45,420 --> 00:31:46,420
Okay.

833
00:31:46,740 --> 00:31:47,900
He plays football.

834
00:31:48,950 --> 00:31:50,240
She cooks food.

835
00:31:51,120 --> 00:31:52,680
It rains in summer.

836
00:31:53,480 --> 00:31:53,760
Good.

837
00:31:54,300 --> 00:31:55,760
Now make a few sentences yourself.

838
00:31:56,910 --> 00:31:58,040
He reads a book.

839
00:31:59,100 --> 00:32:00,320
She sings a song.

840
00:32:01,220 --> 00:32:02,700
It shines in the sky.

841
00:32:03,510 --> 00:32:04,510
Excellent.

842
00:32:04,980 --> 00:32:06,360
You used S correctly.

843
00:32:07,640 --> 00:32:14,020
Now remember, when we use I, you,
we, or they, we don't add S.

844
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:16,880
For example, I play football.

845
00:32:17,600 --> 00:32:18,600
We study English.

846
00:32:19,360 --> 00:32:20,360
They eat lunch.

847
00:32:21,260 --> 00:32:22,260
I see.

848
00:32:22,580 --> 00:32:25,700
So I play, but he plays.

849
00:32:26,660 --> 00:32:27,660
Exactly.

850
00:32:27,720 --> 00:32:28,720
That's the rule.

851
00:32:28,860 --> 00:32:30,300
Let's repeat it a few times together.

852
00:32:30,301 --> 00:32:31,820
I play.

853
00:32:32,760 --> 00:32:33,760
He plays.

854
00:32:34,380 --> 00:32:35,380
I read.

855
00:32:35,900 --> 00:32:36,900
She reads.

856
00:32:37,320 --> 00:32:38,320
I cook.

857
00:32:38,420 --> 00:32:39,420
She cooks.

858
00:32:39,920 --> 00:32:40,920
I go.

859
00:32:41,160 --> 00:32:42,160
He goes.

860
00:32:42,500 --> 00:32:43,500
Wonderful.

861
00:32:44,160 --> 00:32:45,160
You are learning fast.

862
00:32:45,840 --> 00:32:49,960
You see, English becomes easy when we
break it into small steps.

863
00:32:50,580 --> 00:32:51,580
Yes, sir.

864
00:32:52,100 --> 00:32:53,720
I feel more confident now.

865
00:32:53,721 --> 00:32:55,060
That's great.

866
00:32:55,665 --> 00:32:59,660
Now let's practice questions again using
do and does.

867
00:33:00,470 --> 00:33:04,720
You can ask, do you like apples or does he
like apples?

868
00:33:05,400 --> 00:33:06,400
Okay.

869
00:33:06,780 --> 00:33:07,840
Do you like music?

870
00:33:08,840 --> 00:33:09,840
Yes, I do.

871
00:33:10,430 --> 00:33:11,600
Does she like music?

872
00:33:12,400 --> 00:33:13,400
Yes, she does.

873
00:33:14,010 --> 00:33:15,010
Very good.

874
00:33:15,310 --> 00:33:17,600
Let's try negative sentences, too.

875
00:33:18,500 --> 00:33:19,660
I don't like coffee.

876
00:33:20,970 --> 00:33:22,500
He doesn't like milk.

877
00:33:23,560 --> 00:33:24,840
I don't like coffee.

878
00:33:25,880 --> 00:33:27,320
He doesn't like milk.

879
00:33:27,960 --> 00:33:28,960
Great.

880
00:33:29,240 --> 00:33:33,260
Always remember, after doesn't,
we don't add S to the verb.

881
00:33:33,820 --> 00:33:37,060
So he doesn't like, not he doesn't like.

882
00:33:37,920 --> 00:33:38,920
Yes, sir.

883
00:33:39,260 --> 00:33:40,300
I will remember that.

884
00:33:40,880 --> 00:33:41,220
Good.

885
00:33:41,780 --> 00:33:43,580
Now let's use this in a small
conversation.

886
00:33:44,560 --> 00:33:45,140
I will ask.

887
00:33:45,580 --> 00:33:46,580
You answer.

888
00:33:46,780 --> 00:33:47,780
Do you get up early?

889
00:33:48,605 --> 00:33:49,605
Yes, I do.

890
00:33:50,410 --> 00:33:51,620
What time do you wake up?

891
00:33:52,500 --> 00:33:54,700
I wake up at seven o'clock.

892
00:33:55,320 --> 00:33:56,320
Do you eat breakfast?

893
00:33:57,200 --> 00:33:59,480
Yes, I eat breakfast every day.

894
00:34:00,220 --> 00:34:01,220
What do you eat?

895
00:34:01,660 --> 00:34:03,520
I eat bread and eggs.

896
00:34:04,540 --> 00:34:05,860
What do you do after breakfast?

897
00:34:06,870 --> 00:34:07,900
I go to school.

898
00:34:08,680 --> 00:34:09,680
Excellent.

899
00:34:09,980 --> 00:34:12,320
You just had a small talk about your daily
life.

900
00:34:13,170 --> 00:34:16,880
Sir, now I understand how to talk with
others.

901
00:34:17,600 --> 00:34:20,280
I can ask and answer simple questions.

902
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:22,000
That's right.

903
00:34:22,220 --> 00:34:26,080
You can talk about yourself, your family,
and your daily routine.

904
00:34:26,920 --> 00:34:29,240
For example, my mother cooks breakfast.

905
00:34:30,160 --> 00:34:31,660
My father goes to work.

906
00:34:32,400 --> 00:34:33,400
My sister studies.

907
00:34:34,300 --> 00:34:36,860
These are all simple, present-tent
sentences.

908
00:34:37,750 --> 00:34:39,240
My mother cooks food.

909
00:34:39,980 --> 00:34:41,740
My father drives a car.

910
00:34:42,420 --> 00:34:44,080
My sister goes to school.

911
00:34:44,740 --> 00:34:45,740
Perfect.

912
00:34:45,880 --> 00:34:46,880
You are improving.

913
00:34:47,650 --> 00:34:49,880
Now, if someone laughs, just smile.

914
00:34:50,700 --> 00:34:51,940
You know that you are learning.

915
00:34:52,360 --> 00:34:55,275
They may laugh today,
but one day they will listen

916
00:34:55,276 --> 00:34:59,040
carefully because your English
will be clear and confident.

917
00:35:00,150 --> 00:35:01,280
I hope so, sir.

918
00:35:01,940 --> 00:35:03,700
I want to speak like you one day.

919
00:35:04,480 --> 00:35:05,480
You will.

920
00:35:05,800 --> 00:35:07,600
Just keep speaking every day.

921
00:35:08,160 --> 00:35:09,360
Practice in front of a mirror.

922
00:35:09,920 --> 00:35:10,920
Talk to yourself.

923
00:35:11,480 --> 00:35:13,160
Say things like, I wake up.

924
00:35:13,640 --> 00:35:14,640
I wash my face.

925
00:35:15,400 --> 00:35:16,400
I go out.

926
00:35:16,540 --> 00:35:17,540
I meet my friends.

927
00:35:18,300 --> 00:35:19,300
Repeat and repeat.

928
00:35:20,060 --> 00:35:21,060
I can do that.

929
00:35:21,530 --> 00:35:23,900
I can practice in my room every morning.

930
00:35:24,720 --> 00:35:25,720
That's a great idea.

931
00:35:26,440 --> 00:35:28,740
You can also write short notes about your
day.

932
00:35:29,290 --> 00:35:31,840
For example, write, I go to school.

933
00:35:32,380 --> 00:35:33,380
I study English.

934
00:35:33,960 --> 00:35:34,960
I talk with my teacher.

935
00:35:35,700 --> 00:35:36,940
Writing helps you remember.

936
00:35:37,580 --> 00:35:38,580
Yes, sir.

937
00:35:38,920 --> 00:35:39,960
I like writing, too.

938
00:35:40,640 --> 00:35:41,640
Wonderful.

939
00:35:41,830 --> 00:35:43,440
Keep writing and reading aloud.

940
00:35:44,240 --> 00:35:46,660
Listen to English songs or short stories.

941
00:35:47,300 --> 00:35:48,300
Try to repeat them.

942
00:35:48,840 --> 00:35:51,000
Your tongue will become used to English
sounds.

943
00:35:52,090 --> 00:35:53,240
I will do that, sir.

944
00:35:53,840 --> 00:35:55,620
Thank you for helping me feel better.

945
00:35:55,621 --> 00:35:57,600
You are very welcome.

946
00:35:58,340 --> 00:36:01,620
Remember, learning English is not about
being perfect.

947
00:36:02,590 --> 00:36:06,500
It's about being brave enough to speak
even when others laugh.

948
00:36:07,320 --> 00:36:09,220
Every time you speak, you improve.

949
00:36:10,120 --> 00:36:12,720
Every time you try, you win a small
victory.

950
00:36:13,730 --> 00:36:14,920
I understand now, sir.

951
00:36:15,380 --> 00:36:16,820
I will not stop speaking.

952
00:36:17,500 --> 00:36:19,060
I will keep trying every day.

953
00:36:19,930 --> 00:36:20,930
That's the spirit.

954
00:36:21,380 --> 00:36:22,420
You are doing great.

955
00:36:24,575 --> 00:36:27,380
Sir, today I tried to speak English again
with my friends.

956
00:36:28,020 --> 00:36:30,980
I spoke slowly, but they still laughed a
little.

957
00:36:31,690 --> 00:36:33,560
This time, I didn't feel too bad.

958
00:36:34,140 --> 00:36:36,660
I remembered what you said and I just
smiled.

959
00:36:37,500 --> 00:36:38,620
But I want to speak better.

960
00:36:39,320 --> 00:36:41,740
I want people to listen to me,
not laugh.

961
00:36:42,645 --> 00:36:43,780
I am very proud of you.

962
00:36:44,210 --> 00:36:46,090
You didn't stop speaking even when they
laughed.

963
00:36:46,680 --> 00:36:47,640
That's real courage.

964
00:36:47,641 --> 00:36:50,420
Every time you speak, you become better.

965
00:36:51,170 --> 00:36:53,560
Tell me, what did you say to your friends
today?

966
00:36:54,440 --> 00:36:57,900
I said, I wake up early and I go to
school.

967
00:36:58,600 --> 00:37:01,840
Then I told them, I study English every
day.

968
00:37:02,360 --> 00:37:04,960
But one word I said wrong and they
laughed.

969
00:37:05,760 --> 00:37:06,760
That's okay.

970
00:37:07,420 --> 00:37:09,298
Maybe they don't
understand what learning

971
00:37:09,299 --> 00:37:11,820
feels like, but you are
learning the right way.

972
00:37:11,821 --> 00:37:14,880
You used the simple present tense very
well.

973
00:37:15,500 --> 00:37:16,500
I wake up early.

974
00:37:17,120 --> 00:37:18,120
I go to school.

975
00:37:18,320 --> 00:37:19,320
I study English.

976
00:37:19,620 --> 00:37:20,740
Those are perfect sentences.

977
00:37:21,690 --> 00:37:23,920
When I speak like that, I feel calm.

978
00:37:24,520 --> 00:37:25,660
I don't need big words.

979
00:37:26,240 --> 00:37:28,360
I just want to speak correctly and
clearly.

980
00:37:29,200 --> 00:37:29,520
Exactly.

981
00:37:30,190 --> 00:37:32,360
Simple English is powerful English.

982
00:37:33,160 --> 00:37:36,480
Most people in the world speak using
short, clear sentences.

983
00:37:37,300 --> 00:37:38,300
You can do the same.

984
00:37:38,660 --> 00:37:40,620
Let's talk about more things you do every
day.

985
00:37:41,320 --> 00:37:42,320
What time do you wake up?

986
00:37:43,310 --> 00:37:44,980
I wake up at seven o'clock.

987
00:37:45,815 --> 00:37:47,260
What do you do after you wake up?

988
00:37:48,015 --> 00:37:49,400
I brush my teeth.

989
00:37:50,140 --> 00:37:51,220
I wash my face.

990
00:37:52,000 --> 00:37:53,000
I eat breakfast.

991
00:37:53,640 --> 00:37:54,640
Excellent.

992
00:37:54,880 --> 00:37:56,080
What do you eat for breakfast?

993
00:37:56,900 --> 00:37:58,300
I eat bread and eggs.

994
00:37:58,840 --> 00:38:00,400
Sometimes I drink milk.

995
00:38:01,220 --> 00:38:02,220
That's great.

996
00:38:02,520 --> 00:38:04,140
Now tell me what you do after breakfast.

997
00:38:05,165 --> 00:38:06,165
I go to school.

998
00:38:06,760 --> 00:38:07,760
I study.

999
00:38:08,020 --> 00:38:09,240
I talk to my teacher.

1000
00:38:10,040 --> 00:38:11,200
I play with my friends.

1001
00:38:11,840 --> 00:38:12,840
Very good.

1002
00:38:13,120 --> 00:38:15,360
You are making perfect daily routine
sentences.

1003
00:38:16,180 --> 00:38:17,540
You can even make them longer now.

1004
00:38:18,120 --> 00:38:20,620
You can say, I go to school at eight o
'clock.

1005
00:38:21,020 --> 00:38:22,320
I study English in science.

1006
00:38:22,980 --> 00:38:24,820
I play with my friends during break time.

1007
00:38:25,280 --> 00:38:26,280
Try it.

1008
00:38:26,490 --> 00:38:28,320
I go to school at eight o'clock.

1009
00:38:28,800 --> 00:38:30,400
I study English in science.

1010
00:38:31,080 --> 00:38:33,480
I play with my friends during break time.

1011
00:38:33,481 --> 00:38:34,481
Wonderful.

1012
00:38:35,200 --> 00:38:36,640
You see how fluent you sound now?

1013
00:38:37,120 --> 00:38:37,740
Yes, sir.

1014
00:38:38,120 --> 00:38:41,160
When I speak slowly, I can say everything
clearly.

1015
00:38:41,900 --> 00:38:42,900
That's right.

1016
00:38:43,000 --> 00:38:46,500
You are speaking clearly and that is more
important than speaking fast.

1017
00:38:47,260 --> 00:38:49,460
You can practice by talking about your
afternoon too.

1018
00:38:50,135 --> 00:38:51,495
What do you do when you come home?

1019
00:38:51,860 --> 00:38:52,860
I eat lunch.

1020
00:38:53,540 --> 00:38:54,540
Then I take a rest.

1021
00:38:55,120 --> 00:38:56,120
I do my homework.

1022
00:38:56,760 --> 00:38:58,500
After that, I help my mother.

1023
00:38:58,650 --> 00:38:59,650
Excellent.

1024
00:39:00,200 --> 00:39:03,360
You are using verbs correctly in the
simple present tense.

1025
00:39:04,060 --> 00:39:06,420
Eat, take, do, help.

1026
00:39:06,940 --> 00:39:08,080
These are all action words.

1027
00:39:08,920 --> 00:39:10,360
They show what you do every day.

1028
00:39:11,000 --> 00:39:11,640
Yes, sir.

1029
00:39:11,980 --> 00:39:12,980
I understand now.

1030
00:39:13,400 --> 00:39:17,200
The simple present tense is about things I
do every day.

1031
00:39:17,800 --> 00:39:18,800
Exactly.

1032
00:39:18,900 --> 00:39:21,140
And also about things you like or don't
like.

1033
00:39:21,780 --> 00:39:22,780
Let's practice that.

1034
00:39:23,150 --> 00:39:24,590
What do you like to do after school?

1035
00:39:25,390 --> 00:39:26,920
I like to listen to music.

1036
00:39:27,480 --> 00:39:28,480
I like to draw pictures.

1037
00:39:29,300 --> 00:39:30,880
I like to talk with my friends.

1038
00:39:31,360 --> 00:39:32,360
Very good.

1039
00:39:32,520 --> 00:39:33,980
And what don't you like to do?

1040
00:39:34,895 --> 00:39:36,280
I don't like to wash dishes.

1041
00:39:37,060 --> 00:39:38,800
I don't like to wake up very early.

1042
00:39:39,420 --> 00:39:41,360
I don't like to fight with my brother.

1043
00:39:41,960 --> 00:39:42,960
Great.

1044
00:39:43,020 --> 00:39:44,960
That's how you express your feelings in
English.

1045
00:39:45,740 --> 00:39:46,040
I like.

1046
00:39:46,540 --> 00:39:47,540
I don't like.

1047
00:39:47,780 --> 00:39:48,780
It's easy and natural.

1048
00:39:49,630 --> 00:39:53,620
Now let's make some sentences about other
people using he and she.

1049
00:39:54,525 --> 00:39:55,600
Tell me about your father.

1050
00:39:56,530 --> 00:39:58,320
My father works in an office.

1051
00:39:58,960 --> 00:39:59,960
He drives a car.

1052
00:40:00,640 --> 00:40:02,100
He drinks tea in the morning.

1053
00:40:02,840 --> 00:40:03,840
Very good.

1054
00:40:04,040 --> 00:40:05,080
Tell me about your mother.

1055
00:40:05,750 --> 00:40:07,120
My mother cooks food.

1056
00:40:07,780 --> 00:40:09,020
She cleans the house.

1057
00:40:09,740 --> 00:40:11,360
She watches TV in the evening.

1058
00:40:12,120 --> 00:40:13,120
Excellent.

1059
00:40:13,240 --> 00:40:14,240
And your brother?

1060
00:40:14,850 --> 00:40:16,400
My brother goes to school.

1061
00:40:17,040 --> 00:40:18,040
He plays football.

1062
00:40:18,400 --> 00:40:19,400
He studies math.

1063
00:40:19,860 --> 00:40:20,860
Perfect.

1064
00:40:21,100 --> 00:40:23,580
You are using he and she sentences very
well.

1065
00:40:24,200 --> 00:40:28,360
Remember, with he, she and it,
we add S to the verb.

1066
00:40:29,240 --> 00:40:31,660
Works, drives, plays, studies.

1067
00:40:32,640 --> 00:40:33,180
Yes, sir.

1068
00:40:33,560 --> 00:40:34,860
I remember that rule now.

1069
00:40:35,360 --> 00:40:35,580
Good.

1070
00:40:36,180 --> 00:40:37,300
Now let's make it more fun.

1071
00:40:37,880 --> 00:40:40,940
I will see a sentence and you tell me if
it's correct or not.

1072
00:40:41,640 --> 00:40:43,120
He play football.

1073
00:40:43,880 --> 00:40:44,880
It's wrong.

1074
00:40:45,120 --> 00:40:46,920
It should be he plays football.

1075
00:40:47,840 --> 00:40:48,840
Excellent.

1076
00:40:49,040 --> 00:40:50,280
She go to school.

1077
00:40:50,980 --> 00:40:51,980
Wrong.

1078
00:40:52,060 --> 00:40:53,120
She goes to school.

1079
00:40:54,210 --> 00:40:55,440
They like tea.

1080
00:40:56,120 --> 00:40:57,120
Wrong.

1081
00:40:57,240 --> 00:40:58,240
They like tea.

1082
00:40:58,820 --> 00:40:59,820
Very good.

1083
00:40:59,980 --> 00:41:01,060
You are becoming confident.

1084
00:41:01,740 --> 00:41:02,740
Thank you, sir.

1085
00:41:03,040 --> 00:41:05,360
I feel better when I can find mistakes
myself.

1086
00:41:06,240 --> 00:41:07,360
That's the sign of progress.

1087
00:41:08,200 --> 00:41:10,920
Now let's practice some questions you can
use in daily life.

1088
00:41:11,440 --> 00:41:13,560
For example, what do you eat for lunch?

1089
00:41:14,380 --> 00:41:15,580
What time do you go to school?

1090
00:41:16,300 --> 00:41:17,340
Do you like reading books?

1091
00:41:18,450 --> 00:41:19,520
What do you eat for lunch?

1092
00:41:20,460 --> 00:41:21,700
I eat rice and vegetables.

1093
00:41:22,760 --> 00:41:24,180
What time do you go to school?

1094
00:41:25,140 --> 00:41:26,940
I go to school at eight o'clock.

1095
00:41:27,680 --> 00:41:29,000
Do you like reading books?

1096
00:41:29,740 --> 00:41:30,740
Yes, I do.

1097
00:41:30,920 --> 00:41:32,160
I like reading English stories.

1098
00:41:33,055 --> 00:41:36,600
I want to read English stories too,
but I find them difficult.

1099
00:41:36,601 --> 00:41:37,601
That's normal.

1100
00:41:38,460 --> 00:41:39,460
Start with short stories.

1101
00:41:40,120 --> 00:41:41,120
Read slowly.

1102
00:41:41,200 --> 00:41:42,960
When you find a new word, don't stop.

1103
00:41:43,440 --> 00:41:45,000
Try to understand from the sentence.

1104
00:41:45,900 --> 00:41:46,900
Then read aloud.

1105
00:41:47,340 --> 00:41:48,720
Reading aloud helps your speaking.

1106
00:41:49,680 --> 00:41:50,680
I can do that.

1107
00:41:50,945 --> 00:41:52,820
I will read one page every day.

1108
00:41:53,430 --> 00:41:54,560
That's a wonderful plan.

1109
00:41:55,200 --> 00:41:59,380
When you read, say the sentences in your
mind and then repeat them out loud.

1110
00:42:00,080 --> 00:42:01,840
For example, I wake up.

1111
00:42:02,320 --> 00:42:03,320
I eat breakfast.

1112
00:42:04,250 --> 00:42:07,520
When you speak again and again,
your mouth remembers the sound.

1113
00:42:08,180 --> 00:42:09,180
Yes, sir.

1114
00:42:09,380 --> 00:42:11,060
When I repeat, it feels easier.

1115
00:42:11,700 --> 00:42:12,700
Exactly.

1116
00:42:13,000 --> 00:42:14,820
Listening and repeating is the best
practice.

1117
00:42:15,640 --> 00:42:18,680
You can listen to small English videos or
short podcasts.

1118
00:42:19,500 --> 00:42:20,500
Listen carefully.

1119
00:42:20,700 --> 00:42:22,540
Pause and repeat what they say.

1120
00:42:23,470 --> 00:42:27,800
I listen to English songs sometimes,
but I don't understand all the words.

1121
00:42:28,540 --> 00:42:29,540
That's okay.

1122
00:42:29,570 --> 00:42:31,980
You can enjoy the rhythm and catch small
words.

1123
00:42:31,981 --> 00:42:36,660
Even when you don't understand everything,
your ears get used to English sounds.

1124
00:42:37,310 --> 00:42:39,580
Slowly, you will start to understand more.

1125
00:42:40,260 --> 00:42:41,260
That's true.

1126
00:42:41,820 --> 00:42:44,460
Sometimes, I understand a few words and
feel happy.

1127
00:42:45,190 --> 00:42:46,260
That's a great feeling.

1128
00:42:46,920 --> 00:42:47,920
Celebrate small progress.

1129
00:42:48,700 --> 00:42:51,020
Each new word you understand is a step
forward.

1130
00:42:51,600 --> 00:42:52,960
You are not competing with anyone.

1131
00:42:53,360 --> 00:42:54,560
You are learning for yourself.

1132
00:42:55,220 --> 00:42:56,220
Yes, sir.

1133
00:42:56,280 --> 00:42:59,500
I want to speak English so I can talk to
people everywhere.

1134
00:43:00,490 --> 00:43:01,540
That's a wonderful goal.

1135
00:43:02,520 --> 00:43:04,160
English helps you connect with the world.

1136
00:43:04,600 --> 00:43:06,820
But remember, it's not about being
perfect.

1137
00:43:07,520 --> 00:43:08,520
It's about being brave.

1138
00:43:09,460 --> 00:43:11,300
When you speak, speak with confidence.

1139
00:43:12,270 --> 00:43:14,480
Even if you make a small mistake,
keep talking.

1140
00:43:15,320 --> 00:43:16,320
I will try, sir.

1141
00:43:16,665 --> 00:43:18,340
I want to be brave when I speak.

1142
00:43:19,200 --> 00:43:20,380
You already are brave.

1143
00:43:21,120 --> 00:43:22,700
You speak even when others laugh.

1144
00:43:23,340 --> 00:43:24,340
That shows strength.

1145
00:43:25,040 --> 00:43:27,520
Every time you use English, your brain
becomes stronger.

1146
00:43:27,521 --> 00:43:31,460
Every sentence you say brings you closer
to fluency.

1147
00:43:32,180 --> 00:43:33,180
I understand now.

1148
00:43:33,580 --> 00:43:35,960
I just need to keep going, not stop.

1149
00:43:36,890 --> 00:43:39,560
Yes, make English part of your daily life.

1150
00:43:40,000 --> 00:43:41,640
When you wake up, say good morning.

1151
00:43:42,320 --> 00:43:44,240
When you eat, say I eat breakfast.

1152
00:43:45,100 --> 00:43:46,740
When you sleep, say good night.

1153
00:43:47,560 --> 00:43:49,440
Talk in English to yourself every day.

1154
00:43:50,240 --> 00:43:51,240
I can do that easily.

1155
00:43:51,900 --> 00:43:54,480
I can speak small sentences while doing
things.

1156
00:43:54,481 --> 00:43:55,760
That's perfect.

1157
00:43:56,480 --> 00:43:58,821
That's how children
learn their first language

1158
00:43:58,822 --> 00:44:01,781
by speaking small
sentences again and again.

1159
00:44:01,880 --> 00:44:02,880
You can do the same.

1160
00:44:03,850 --> 00:44:04,850
Thank you, sir.

1161
00:44:04,980 --> 00:44:06,620
You make English feel simple.

1162
00:44:07,490 --> 00:44:09,580
Because it is simple when you use it
daily.

1163
00:44:10,380 --> 00:44:12,340
Don't wait for big lessons or big words.

1164
00:44:13,020 --> 00:44:14,420
Just speak what you know.

1165
00:44:15,020 --> 00:44:17,720
Smile, be confident and enjoy the process.

1166
00:44:18,260 --> 00:44:19,260
Yes, sir.

1167
00:44:19,560 --> 00:44:21,240
I feel more confident now.

1168
00:44:21,640 --> 00:44:25,620
I will speak English every day no matter
what people say.

1169
00:44:26,330 --> 00:44:28,260
That's the best promise you can make to
yourself.

